        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 5:29PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Billings, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crow Indian Reservation.

This does not include the City of Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
